id=qid::label=str::sort=i::class_name=lstr::name=lstr::master=r::final_master=r::sex=lstr::height=i::weight=i::attr=lstr::power=str::magic=str::durability=str::luck=str::agile=str::noble_phantasm=str::detail=lstr::class_skill_name_1=lstr::class_skill_1=lstr::class_skill_filename_1=str::class_skill_unlock_1=str::class_skill_unlock_filename_1=str::class_skill_name_2=lstr::class_skill_2=lstr::class_skill_filename_2=str::class_skill_unlock_2=str::class_skill_unlock_filename_2=str::skill_name_1=lstr::skill_1=lstr::skill_filename_1=str::skill_unlock_1=str::skill_unlock_filename_1=str::skill_name_2=lstr::skill_2=lstr::skill_filename_2=str::skill_unlock_2=str::skill_unlock_filename_2=str::skill_name_3=lstr::skill_3=lstr::skill_filename_3=str::skill_unlock_3=str::skill_unlock_filename_3=str::skill_name_4=lstr::skill_4=lstr::skill_filename_4=str::skill_unlock_4=str::skill_unlock_filename_4=str::skill_name_5=lstr::skill_5=lstr::skill_filename_5=str::skill_unlock_5=str::skill_unlock_filename_5=str::np_index_1=i::np_filename_1=str::np_name_1=lstr::np_sub_1=lstr::np_rank_1=lstr::np_type_1=lstr::np_range_1=lstr::np_capture_1=lstr::np_def_target_1=lstr::np_explanation_1=lstr::np_index_2=i::np_filename_2=str::np_name_2=lstr::np_sub_2=lstr::np_rank_2=lstr::np_type_2=lstr::np_range_2=lstr::np_capture_2=lstr::np_def_target_2=lstr::np_explanation_2=lstr::np_index_3=i::np_filename_3=str::np_name_3=lstr::np_sub_3=lstr::np_rank_3=lstr::np_type_3=lstr::np_range_3=lstr::np_capture_3=lstr::np_def_target_3=lstr::np_explanation_3=lstr::
1::Ð£ÐÊÐÐ¥::1::Saber::Altria::1::1::Female::154::42::Lawful-Good::B::B::C::B::C::C::King Arthur, the legendary hero of England, is immortalized as "The Once and Future King."		He is a hero who is widely known as an icon of chivalry; however, he is not just a legend, but also somone who is said to have actually existed.		In his earliest chronicles, the real King Arthur is called "Dux Bellorum," the king of war, a great general who led the twelve kings of Northern England (the Gododdin) against other tribes, like the Picts and Scots. There are several theories about the identity of this great general, and some say the king may correspond to two different historical figures. One is Arthur, the Briton. The other is Artorius, the Roman. The accomplishments of both have synthesized into the legend of King Arthur, still famous to this day.		Arthur became king after drawing a sword upon whose blade Merlin the mage had inscribed the words, "The one who pulls this sword from this stone is the King of England." From there, countless stories unfolded about King Arthur and his Knights of the Round Table.		He was born of a tryst between Uther Pendragon, King of the Britons, and blue-eyed Igraine, wife to the Duke of Cornwall. Paying the price for pursuing his love, King Uther enlisted the help of Merlin, entrusting the mage with the child born between himself and Igraine.		Vowing to rescue Arthurãwho carried a great destinyãfrom the royal crisis and guide him onto the correct path, Merlin placed him in the care of Sir Ector, Uther's loyal knight. Ector adopted Arthur as his own son, raising him until the day he drew the sword of appointment.		The trials and travails that awaited Arthur after pulling out the sword and becoming king would later fill the tapestries of history, becoming a grand narrative that is representative of chivalry in the Middle Ages. King Arthur's accomplishments while reigning over Camelotãthe White City, and saving England alongside his many great knights cemented him as a hero. His famous sword, Excalibur, is not the sword of appointment; it is the sacred sword that Arthur received from the Lady of the Lake, under Merlin's guidance, after the sword of appointment was lost.		The Lady of the Lake, Vivian, became Arthur's fairy guardian after bestowing him with Excalibur. Morgan le Fay, Arthur's lifelong nemesis, exists as his guardian fairy Vivian's obverse. However, as a fairy of the lake herself, she too was sworn to protect the king. King Arthur commanded his Knights of the Round Table to seek out the Holy Grail.		This search for the Holy Grail is central to Arthurian legend, but ultimately only three knights were dispatched, and Arthur himself did not journey with them. The peerless knight Lancelot could not reach the Grail due to the stain of infidelity on his heart. His son, Galahad, was able to obtain the grail but chose to relinquish it. In the end, the legend closes with King Arthur's death.		Arthur's life is punctuated by clashes with Morgan, his half-sister from a different father, as she attempted to kill him many times. and his legend is ended by his bitter conflict with Mordred, the knight who was born from Morgan's orchestrations. King Arthur's fall begins when his most trusted knight, Lancelot, disappears after dishonoring himself by adultering with the King's wife, Guinevere. Losing his trusted companion, his holy scabbard, and even control of his kingdom over the course of his final journey, King Arthur sees his final battle at Camlann. On the verge of his death, he entrusts Excalibur to Sir Bedivere, who returns it to the Lady of the Lake. 		King Arthur's body is transported by the Ladies of the Lake to Avalon, the land where heroes sleep. It was then foretold that in England's hour of greatest need, Arthur would awaken from his slumber and save his country once again.		Arthur carries the red dragonãthe symbol of the Britons on his back, and he himself also bears the dragon attribute. Because he carries the attribute of a dragon, a creature that is the embodiment of Mystics and predominance, he has a powerful magical energy characteristic. However, he is not well-matched against Servants who have a background in dragon slaying.::Magic Resistance: A::Cancel all magecraft below A.	In reality, modern mages cannot hurt Saber.::40_skill_00_00::::::Riding: B::The riding ability.	Can ride most things better than the average person, 	but can't ride beasts that are demonic and holy rank beasts.::40_skill_00_01::::::Intuition: A::The ability to constantly "sense" the best course of action for oneself during battle.		A well-honed sixth sense is akin to precognition. It reduces disturbances that interfere with vision and hearing by half.::40_skill_00_10::::::Mana Burst: A::It wraps magical energy around her weapon or her own body, and improves its abilities by releasing that energy in an instant. In other words, it is a jet thruster made of magical energy.		Not only does Saber use magical energy for swordplay, she also utilizes it for defense and movement. She is able to fight Berserker despite having the physique of a young girl because of her massive amount of magical energy.		An ordinary weapon that has no powerful divine protection cannot endure her magical energy-filled attacks and would be destroyed with a single blow.::40_chara_00b::B20::40_skill_00_11::Charisma: B::The natural ability to command corps.	It improves one's own army's skill in group battles.		Charisma is a rare ability and being B rank is said to be enough for a king of a country.::40_skill_00_12::::::::::::::::::::::::::0::41_atrus_14a::Barrier of the Wind King::Invisible Air::C::Anti-Personnel::1~2::1 item::::The unseen sword.	It doesn't let the enemy know the weapon's distance; it is simple, but proves to be tremendously effective in hand-to-hand combat.	It is a Noble Phantasm protected by a powerful magecraft, so it does not mean that the sword itself is invisible.		The sword blade sheathed in wind changes the refractive index of light and makes the original shape of the sword invisible. It is not exactly a vacuum state, but the wind wrapped around the blade itself is a lethal weapon and seems to increase the destructive power of slashing attacks. It can only create a vacuum state in the instant that the compressed wind is released.		In instances where the target of the attack has "resistance to modifications caused by visual disturbances", modification of hit accuracy due to Barrier of the Wind King will be ineffective.		In addition to making the blade invisible, it can also release the compressed wind and shoot it as a single-use projectile weapon. 	In that case, the damage is limited and isn't affected by Saber's own magical energy or physical strength.::1::41_atrus_01a::Yakusoku Sareta Shouri No Ken::Excalibur::A++::Anti-Fortress::1~99::1000 persons::::The sword of light.	It is not a man-made weapon, but a Divine Construct forged by the stars.		Within the category of holy swords, it is the greatest Noble Phantasm.		It is a holy sword that converts the user's magical energy into "light," increases momentum by convergence and acceleration, and makes it possible to use magical energy at the level of a Divine Spirit.		To an outsider it looks like a large belt of light, but it actually only has a hitbox at the tip of the light. It is "the ultimate slashing attack" that cuts through everything along the "faults" that are formed by the light.		That massive magical energy gives heat to everything other than the tip as well, and as a result it all gets taken by a wave of light that mows down everything above the ground. It could even be called a directional energy weapon.::2::41_atrus_00a::Ever the Distant Utopia ::Avalon::EX::Barrier::::::1 person::The ability of Excalibur's sheath.		The third Noble Phantasm that was lost.		The sheath of the holy sword was excavated in Cornwall by Einzbern and returned to its owner across the ages.		In the legend of King Arthur, the true ability of the holy sword is "the power of immortality" that comes from this sheath.		It has the ability to heal its owner's wounds and stop aging, but in actuality, it is what can be referred to as a "mobile fortress" that targets an individual.		By unsheathing it and putting oneself in the home of the fairies, one can shut out any physical interference.		It can even prevent interference from parallel worlds, an example of True Magic.::
2::ÐÂÐ¥ÐÐÈÐ¥::3::Archer::EMIYA::2::2::Male::187::78::Neutral-Balanced::D::B::C::E::C::??::The hero version of Shirou Emiya, created by a miracle.		A hard-as-nails Heroic Spirit that can manifest many weapons and master the Reality Marble without penalty.		Everything else about him is unknown...::Magic Resistance: D::Nullifies usage of magecraft in one step (single action).	Magic resistance that is comparable to that of a magic protection amulet.::40_skill_01_00::::::Independent Action: B::The ability to be independent for a while even if the supply of magical energy from one's Master runs out.	If they are a B Rank, it is possible to stay in this world for two days even if they lose their Master.::40_skill_01_01::::::Clairvoyance: C::How good one's vision is.		The improvement of dynamic vision to capture distant targets.		The higher ranks can even make clairvoyance and foresight possible.::40_skill_01_10::::::Magecraft: C-::Acquires orthodox magecraft.		The proficient category is unknown.::40_skill_01_11::::::Mind's Eye (True): B::The insight accumulated from practice and training.		The "logic of battle" that calmly grasps one's own situation and the enemy's ability, and figures out the remaining means of survival in a predicament.		If there is even a 1% chance of turning things around, then an opportunity to carry out that plan will come.::40_skill_01_12::::::::::::::::::::::::::0::41_atrus_15a::Infinite Sword Creation::Unlimited Blade Works::E~A++::???::???::???::::Special magecraft that Archer uses, known as a Reality Marble.		It replicates weapons that he has visually recognized.	However, replicated weapons are degraded by one rank.		Defensive equipment can be replicated as well, but they require two to three times the magical energy of a typical Projection.::0::::::::::::::::::::0::::::::::::::::::::
3::ÐˋÐ°ÐçÐ¥::2::Lancer::Cû¤ Chulainn::6::6::Male::185::70::Lawful-Balanced::B::C::C::E::A::B::The great hero of Ireland.		The demigod hero born of Lugh, god of light, and the King of Ulster Conchobar's young sister, Deichtine. His childhood name was Sûˋtanta, and he was predicted to "live as a hero." Cû¤ Chulainn means "Culann's savage dog."		When Sûˋtanta was young, he accidentally killed the guard dog of a wealthy merchant, Culann. Sûˋtanta swore, "If this dog has a child, I'll raise it to be strong and loyal like him. Until then, I shall protect you with my life." Hence, the name.		As an adult, Cû¤ Chulainn would travel to the demon-infested Land of Shadows to win the hand of his future wife. After overcoming many obstacles, he arrives in the Land of Shadows and earns the favor of the witch ScûÀthach. ScûÀthach was the ruler of the Land of Shadows, and under her, Cû¤ Chulainn learned many magical and physical techniques. Subsequently, he acquires the weapon that would come to represent him, the demonic spear known as GûÀe Bolg. He leaves the Land of Shadows, spear in hand.		According to the legend, Cû¤ Chulainn is a brave, compassionate, and pleasant young man. He defeats his enemies mercilessly in battle, but is a man of integrity who's never broken a promise. Celtic soldiers have a custom. They make an "oath" (Geass), and soldiers who violate their oath fall under a curse. In accordance with his namesake, Cû¤ Chulainn made an oath to never eat dogs for the rest of his life. He tried his best to keep the oath, but it helped cause his death.		In order to protect his country of Ulster, lacking in might as it was, Cû¤ Chulainn exchanged oaths with his enemies, sometimes at his own expense. His famous oaths include the oath he took with his archenemy, Queen Medb, to fight only one soldier a day and the oath he made with his foster father, Fergus, to yield to him in battle. Both of these incidents are invoked in the history of the war between Ulster and the neighboring country of Connacht.		War began when Medb, Queen of Connacht, invaded Ulster. Her aim was to steal Ulster's golden bull to win a bet against her husband. Cû¤ Chulainn led the small Ulster army against the myriad assembled forces of Connacht and drove them back after 7 years of fighting.		At that time, Cû¤ Chulainn captures Medb but releases her, having sworn an oath not to kill women. Ulster and Connacht reconcile in the aftermath, but Queen Medb has Fergus killed in revenge, viewing Cû¤ Chulainn's mercy as an insult.		Eventually, Cû¤ Chulainn would be forced to break all of his oaths. Sapped of all his strength, he is pierced in the side with a spear. Prideful Cû¤ Chulainn refuses to die on the ground and ties his body to a pillar to remain upright.		On the verge of death, he sees an otter floating in the river, drinking its own blood. He lets out a laugh, tickled by its self-destructive hunger. He then dies on his feet. Now a legendary hero, Cû¤ Chulainn attains the divine protection of MorrûÙgan, goddess of war and fate, who had power over death.		Of course, Cû¤ Chulainn immediately starts causing trouble.		First, he rejects MorrûÙgan's protection. This enrages her, and so she takes the forms of many animals and tries to kill him. Cû¤ Chulainn repels all of her attacks and, having bested her, heals her wounds.		MorrûÙgan admires his kindness and integrity and thus resolves to support him from behind the scenes. In order to preserve his pride, she keeps watch over him while taking care not to intervene directly in his predicaments.::Magic Resistance: C::Nullifies magecraft from incantations shorter than two measures.	Doesn't block large-scale magecraft such as grand magecraft or ritual mantras.::40_skill_02_00::::::::::::::::Battle Continuation: A::Doesn't know when to give up.		Makes it possible to fight on the verge of death	and can survive as long as there are no definitive fatal wounds.::40_skill_02_10::::::Disengage: C::The ability to withdraw from battle.		It can also reset a losing battle back to the beginning (the first turn), and reset the conditions of a technique back to their initial value.::40_skill_02_11::::::Runes: B::The possession of Runes, the Magic Crest of Northern Europe.::40_skill_02_12::::::Protection from Arrows: B::Defense against projectile weapons.	As long as the attacker is in vision, any thrown weapon can be tracked and dealt with.		However, it does not apply to attacks from extremely long distance, nor does it apply to attacks that cover a wide area.::40_skill_02_13::::::Divinity: B::Whether or not one has Divine Spirit aptitude.		The higher it is, the more physically mixed with Divine Spirits one is.::40_skill_02_14::::::1::41_atrus_03a::Barbed Spear that Pierces with Death::GûÀe Bolg::B++::Anti-Army::5~40::50 persons::::This special Noble Phantasm unleashes the power of the GûÀe Bolg curse and throws it with its full power.		GûÀe Bolg is originally a javelin, so this is the correct way to use it.		Unlike the Soaring Spear that Plunges with Death, this Noble Phantasm focuses on pure destructive power, blowing away the target like an explosive round.		The damage and form resembles that of "Brionac: The Five Roaring Stars," wielded by Lugh, the Celtic god of light. However, it has a homing ability, making it closer to "Gungnir: Declaration of the Great God," the Noble Phantasm of Odin, the main deity of Northern Europe.::0::41_atrus_04a::Soaring Spear that Plunges with Death::GûÀe Bolg::B::Anti-Personnel::2~4::1 person::::A cursed spear that always pierces one's heart if it strikes. A fatal thrust from the demonic spear, GûÀe Bolg.		Its true ability is to reverse cause and effect, causing the spear to thrust AFTER it has already penetrated the opponent's heart. Since the spear has struck before even being thrust, it is impossible to defend or prevent it. The result has already been decided.		High AGI (agility) cannot prevent GûÀe Bolg.	Instead, high LCK (luck) is necessary to reverse one's fortunes before GûÀe Bolg is activated.::0::::::::::::::::::::
4::ÐˋÐÊÐÐ¥::4::Rider::Medusa::7::3::Female::172::57::Chaotic-Good::C::B::E::D::B::A+::The demigod Gorgon that comes up in Greek mythology who turns anything she sees into stone.		A demon that is often portrayed as the incarnation of a snake.	She is defeated by the hero, Perseus.	However, she also became an object of worship as the Anti-Hero of negative thoughts.		She is the youngest of the three Gorgon sisters, who are:	Stheno (a strong woman),	Euryale (one who flies far),	and Medusa (a woman who dominates).	But she is not immortal, unlike her older sisters.	She lives on the "Shapeless Isle" near the island where golden apples grow.	They were originally beautiful women, but because they were loved by the sea god Poseidon, they were hated by the sea god's wife.	The war goddess, Athena, who was jealous of the girls' beautiful hair, turned them into demons.		After they were turned into demons, they secluded themselves inside a lightless temple and only attacked humans whenever they felt that they had to.		Medusa, a victim of the gods' unreasonable doings, was met with the fate of her head being cut off on a whim.	The pure-white Pegasus, who was born from the blood spilt from Medusa's neck, is said to be the son of the sea god, Poseidon.		Category-wise, she is more of a Divine Spirit than a Heroic Spirit. The wide variety of abilities she possesses are a remains of when she was treated like a goddess.::Magic Resistance: B::Nullifies magecraft activated by incantations shorter than three measures.	It is difficult to wound one even using grand magecraft or ritual mantras.::40_skill_03_00::::::Riding: A+::The riding ability. Can even ride mythical beasts and divine beasts as long as they are beasts.	However, this does not apply to dragon species.::40_skill_03_01::::::Mystic Eyes: A+::Possesses the highest level of Mystic Eyes, Cybele.		Can turn anything with MGI under C rank into stone without fail.	Can turn even those of B rank into stone depending on the result of the saving throw.	Those of A rank will not be turned to stone, but will receive a "heavy pressure" that will lower all their abilities by one rank.::40_skill_03_10::::::Independent Action: C::The ability to be independent for a while even if the supply of magical energy from one's Master runs out.		If they are a C Rank, it is possible to stay in this world for one day even if they lose their Master.::40_skill_03_11::::::Monstrous Strength: B::Can amplify one's physical strength temporarily.	The attack characteristic that only demons and beasts have.		Increases one's physical strength by one rank by using it.	The duration depends on the rank of the "Monstrous Strength."::40_chara_03b::13ÌÝÓ´ÐˋÐÊÐÐ¥01(ÓÇ Ì)b::40_skill_03_12::Divinity: E-::Has Divine Spirit aptitude, but most of it has degenerated.		Every time the Heroic Spirit's rank as a beast or demon increases, this decreases.::40_chara_03b::a18::40_skill_03_13::::::::::::0::41_atrus_07a::Self-Seal Dark Temple::Breaker Gorgon::C-::Anti-Personnel::0::1 person::::Self-imposed Mystic Eye Killers.		Will constantly use Mystic Eyes, Cybele, if the seal is lifted.::1::41_atrus_10a::Bridle of Chivalry::Bellerophon::A+::Anti-Army::2~50::300 persons::::All abilities increase by one rank when used.	AC also becomes +100.	A physical attack using a beast from the age of gods with a similar extreme advance that crushes the target.	The maximum speed is said to be 400 to 500 kilometers per hour.	From the protection of the pegasus when used, it is the highest level Noble Phantasm in both offense and defense.		Also, Bellerophon is the name of the boy who rode the pegasus in Greek mythology.::2::41_atrus_13a::Other-Seal Blood Temple::Blood Fort Andromeda::B::Anti-Army::10~40::500 persons::::A Bounded Field of blood.		It dissolves humans that get trapped inside.	The dissolved humans become red blood, absorbed by the Bounded Field's user.		Its original use is to absorb magical energy.::
5::ÐÙÐÈÐ¿Ð¢Ð¥::5::Caster::Medea::8::8::Female::163::51::Neutral-Evil::E::A+::D::B::C::C::The queen of misfortune labeled as a witch in Greek mythology.		Jason, the famous hero in the Argo expedition, interrogated King Pelias, who stole the country from Jason's father, and made a promise that if he came back with the Golden Fleece after traveling to Colchis, King Pelias would return the country to him.		The one who possessed the Golden Fleece was the princess of Colchis, Medea. Although she had learned magecraft as the daughter of King Aeetes, who excelled in it, her personality was far from that of a witch.	Her fate started to derail once the hero, Jason, appeared.		The Goddess Aphrodite supported Jason, and upon seeing that King Colchis was invincible, she controlled the mind of Medea, his daughter, and changed her into a girl who blindly loved Jason.		As a result, Medea ended up betraying her father and her own country over a foreign man, Jason, whom she had never seen.		Medea nullified her father's magecraft and the fire-breathing bull woven with magecraft, allowing Jason to obtain the Golden Fleece. King Colchis was infuriated and went to battle himself to capture Jason so that he wouldn't be able to escape.		To help Jason escape from his pursuit, Medea was used by the goddess again.		Medea boarded the Argo, the ship of the man she loved but only knew by name, and slashed her younger brother, Apsyrtus, to pieces in front of her father in pursuit.		The King mourned, ordering for the pieces of his torn son to be collected.		The Argo escaped pursuit using that opening, and Jason safely returned to his homeland, Iolcos, alive. Upon arrival, Jason tried to get his country back from King Pelias, following through on both the promise, and vengeance for his father. However, King Pelias refused and schemed to kill Jason.		Jason escaped from a tight spot by relying on Medea's magecraft for the third time, and she devised a plan for him.		They invited King Pelias and killed his servant. Medea revived them with her magecraft, and offered to cast this spell of immortality on King Pelias as well.	The King was pleased and willingly gave Medea his body. Naturally, he was slashed into pieces and thrown into the ocean.		Jason thus became King, but his fellow Argonauts didn't approve of Jason's actions and, above all, of Medea's very existence.		She betrayed her country for a man, slashed her younger brother so that she would survive, and then she had deceived the king and usurped the throne.		Medea was degraded as a witch and driven out of the country along with Jason. The two reached Corinth, where they were greeted by the King of Corinth.		In this land, Medea finally gained restful days.		However, having been taken far away from her homeland and feared as a witch, the peace she finally obtained did not last long.		The King of Corinth took a liking to Jason and decided to have him marry his daughter. Jason also chose the King's young daughter and exiled Medea. Her actions after that lived up to her name as a witch.		Medea appeared at Jason's wedding and used magecraft, burning everyone in attendance, including the King of Corinth and his daughter. Letting only Jason live, she left the castle.		The whereabouts of Medea, who left Corinth, are unknown.		It is said that the princess, whose life was filled with nothing but betraying others and being betrayed, became a true witch and continued to wander the lands of Greece.::Territory Creation: A::Creating an advantageous territory for oneself as a mage.	It is possible to form a "temple" that exceeds a "shed."::40_skill_04_00::::::Item Construction: A::Can create a tool tinged with magical energy.	Can even create an elixir of immortality, albeit an imitation.::40_skill_04_01::::::Rapid Words of Divine: A::Can activate magecraft without saying an incantation or connecting with Magic Circuits.		Even great magecraft can be cast in one step (single action). They are words from the age of gods, so modern people cannot pronounce them.::40_skill_04_10::::::Argon Coin: EX::Very valuable.		Can summon dragons, but Caster does not have the ability to summon mythical beasts, so it is not possible for her to use it.::40_skill_04_11::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::0::41_atrus_06a::All Spells Must Be Broken::Rule Breaker::C::Anti-Magecraft::1::1 person::::A dagger that can destroy any magecraft.		An ultimate Anti-Magecraft Noble Phantasm that can return objects Strengthened with magical energy, relations connected by contracts, and lives born from magical energy to how they were "before they were created".		A magecraft weapon that embodies the Divinity of a traitorous witch.		Its offensive strength is as feeble as it looks, with only the lethality of a knife.::0::::::::::::::::::::0::::::::::::::::::::
6::ÐÂÐçÐñÐ°::6::Assassin::Sasaki Kojirou::5::5::Male::176::63::Neutral-Evil::C::E::E::A::A+::??::While his existence is met with suspicion, his name remains widely known as that of a peerless swordsman.	He was a beautiful swordsman who wielded a three-foot-long longsword, Monohoshizao.		He is said to be born in the Eiroku era and became famous during 1605-1612, but the truth is not clear.		The books that feature Sasaki Kojirou have many contradicting time periods, because his name was not even written down in "The Book of Five Rings," written by Miyamoto Musashi, his most worthy opponent.	According to records, Kojirou is from the Echizen Province and studied under Toda Seigen.	He favored the longsword and after defeating the master's younger brother, named himself "Ganryu."		After that, he went around various lands as a martial artist and developed the secret sword technique, Swallow Reversal, that can kill even a flying swallow in the Nishiki River in the Sué Province.		Then, after terrifying swordsmen in different lands, he died fighting Miyamoto Musashi at Funa-shima (what would later become Ganryu-jima) in order to maintain the honor of the domain he served.	Because of his longsword, he could not fight while holding the sheath and discarded it in front of Musashi.	Musashi is believed to have said the famous line, "Kojirou has been defeated," after seeing that.		Miyamoto Musashi holds the record for being one of the best swordsmen in Japan.	Sasaki Kojirou was viewed as a worthy opponent, but his real image is as uncertain as a reflection of the moon on water.		People will say, "There was once someone like that," but the legend of Sasaki Kojirou that has been passed down to the present can only be that of a greatãbut fictionalãswordsman that people fabricated.::Presence Concealment: D::Gets rid of one's presence as a Servant. Fit for covert actions. ::40_skill_05_00::::::::::::::::Swallow Reversal::A mystical anti-personnel sword technique.	Maximum targets: 1 person.	A special move that slashes the opponent with three arcs at the same time.		Apparently, it is one example of something called a Multi-Dimensional Refraction Phenomenon.		It is a fatal sword that is impossible to avoid in a different sense from GûÀe Bolg.::40_skill_05_10::::::Mind's Eye (False): A::Resistance to modifications caused by visual disturbances.		It is the natural ability to predict danger, also known as a sixth sense, or premonition.::40_skill_05_11::::::Vitrify: B+::A mind as serene as a clear mirror or still water.		A mental defense mechanism that nullifies interference with the mind.	Since he is not an assassin, he cannot use the "Presence Concealment" Assassin ability, but he can perform Presence Concealment in the form of a martial artist's blank mind state.::40_skill_05_12::::::Knowledge of the Sowa: B::A special skill where the hitting accuracy does not go down no matter how many times the same move is used on the same opponent.		The attacks can no longer be seen through.::40_skill_05_13::::::::::::::::0::::::::::::::::::::0::::::::::::::::::::0::::::::::::::::::::
7::ÐÐ¥ÐçÐ¥Ð¨Ð¥::7::Berserker::Heracles::4::4::Male::253::311::Chaotic-Madness::A+::A::A::B::A::A::The greatest hero in Greek mythology. The demigod hero is a product of the chief deity, Zeus, and a human woman.		Heracles was skilled in every aspect, but there was a big problem with his personality. During his childhood, he beat his lyre teacher to death over a trivial matter. He then spent his days as a shepherd until adulthood, in order to reform himself into a composed man.		Heracles, who grew up to be a fine young man, accomplished many great deeds that caused the King of Thebes to grant his daughter, Megara, to him. They had two children, and he earned the right to succeed the King. Heracles was young and strong, and had already become an existence that no human could hope to defeat. It seemed as if the rest of Heracles' life with his family was going to be smooth sailing.		However, Zeus' wife, Hera, detested Heracles because he was the child of Zeus and a human, and influenced his fate at every opportunity. Hera instilled madness in Heracles, which made him go insane, and he ended up killing Megara and his two children.		Troubled by the sins that he committed, he received an oracle. He was to atone by becoming a slave for Eurystheus, the man who snatched the kingship that would have originally been his to claim.		Eurystheus was jealous of the strong hero, Heracles, and gave him many difficult tasks, declaring that he would stay a slave until he finished them.		They were all labors that could not be achieved by regular humans. They became widely known as the Twelve Labors of Heracles. There were only ten labors that the gods had imposed as punishment for Heracles' sins, but two more labors were added by Eurystheus because he did not approve of the fulfillment of two of them. But, Heracles managed to complete even those tasks, and it may have been because he had just been granted freedom, but he even received an immortal body as proof of his great deeds.		This marked the beginning of the legend of the greatest hero of Greece, Heracles, who accomplished deeds equivalent to the Argo Expedition and the Trojan War by himself.	However, Heracles' life after that was filled with madness. Hera's hatred was endless, and Heracles, who was supposed to be immortal, was poisoned by one of his wives.		The great hero who fought a competitive battle against the sun god as a human,	was slowly getting killed due to the goddess' persistent jealousy.		While on the verge of his death, Heracles burned his own body which was still afflicted with poison, and entrusted himself to Zeus' judgement. The gods approved of Heracles' great deeds in a conference and prepared a seat for him in Olympus after his death, effectively deifying him.		Heracles went mad many times in Greek mythology, but originally he was an excellent soldier who could use any weapon.		Heracles actually possesses attributes that could allow him to be categorized as any of the regular Servant classes, excluding Caster. The best Noble Phantasm that he owns was earned during the Twelve Labors. It is a bow and arrow called "Nine Lives."::Madness Enhancement: B::It increases the rank of the parameter, but takes away most of one's reasoning.::40_skill_06_00::::::::::::::::Battle Continuation: A::The ability to survive.		Makes it possible to fight on the verge of death and survive as long as there are no definitive fatal wounds.::40_chara_06b::A24b::40_skill_06_10::Mind's Eye (False): B::Avoiding danger by intuition or sixth sense.::40_skill_06_11::::::Valor: A+::The ability to nullify mental interference such as coercion, confusion, and bedazzlement.		It also has the effect of increasing combat damage.	However, because he is currently being Madness Enhanced due to class ability, this skill cannot take effect.::40_chara_06b::11ÌÝÓ´ÐÐ¥ÐçÐ¥Ð¨Ð¥04b::40_skill_06_12::Divinity: A::Whether or not one has Divine Spirit aptitude.	The higher it is, the more physically mixed with Divine Spirits one is.		Being Zeus' son and having been welcomed by the gods after his death, Heracles' Divine Spirit aptitude can be considered to be of the highest class.::40_skill_06_13::::::::::::::::0::41_atrus_11a::???::::B::Anti-Personnel:: -::1 person::::Immortality that was gained	from God's blessing (curse).		Turns the body into sturdy armor.	Nullifies all attacks ranked B or lower.::1::41_atrus_12a::Twelve Labors::God Hand::B::Anti-Personnel:: -::1 person::::A hidden ability.		Become automatically resurrected (Raise) in the event one dies.	Raise has a stock of eleven.		In other words, Berserker will not disappear unless he is defeated twelve times.::0::::::::::::::::::::
8::Ð£ÐÊÐÐ¥ÐˆÐ¨Ð¢::10::Saber::Altria::3::3::Female::154::42::Lawful-Evil::A::A++::A::C::D::A++::The result of Saber being contaminated by a mysterious shadow.		What makes her the strongest is not her ability as a swordsman, but the massive amount of magical energy she has due to possessing an element of the dragon species.		As a Servant who was not supplied with enough magical energy, she could not unleash the same combat power from when she was alive. But in this state, she is able to unleash more destructive power than ever before.		In terms of plain attack power, she is the strongest.::Magic Resistance: B::Nullifies magecraft activated by incantations shorter than three measures.	It is difficult to wound her even using grand magecraft or ritual mantras.	...Because she has taken on dark attributes, her Anti-Magic is lowered.::40_skill_07_00::::::Riding: -::The riding skill is lost.::40_skill_07_01::::::Intuition: B::The ability to constantly "sense" the best course of action for oneself during battle.		Because she is constantly suppressing her brutality, her intuition is dulled.::40_chara_07b::c22::40_skill_07_10::Mana Burst: A::The massive magical energy covers Saber's body with a dense fog without her even realizing.		Her defensive power has improved remarkably due to the black armor and magical energy.::40_chara_07b::c_cs07::40_skill_07_11::Charisma: E::The natural ability to command corps.	It improves one's own army's abilities in group battles.		While her leadership improves, the morale of the soldiers decreases significantly.::40_skill_07_12::::::::::::::::::::::::::0::41_atrus_05a::Yakusoku Sareta Shouri No Ken::Excalibur::A++::Anti-Fortress::1~99::1000 persons::::The black aurora sword.	Because Excalibur is an amplifier that converts the user's magical energy, the light of Darkened Saber's holy sword has also turned black.		Just as Vivian and Morgan coexist with the fairies of the lake, this holy sword also has both good and evil attributes.::0::::::::::::::::::::0::::::::::::::::::::
9::ÓÐÂÐçÐñÐ°::9::Assassin::Hassan-i Sabbah::9::9::Male::215::62::Lawful-Evil::B::C::C::E::A::C::An Anti-Hero.	The leader of the Order of Assassins that has origins in the Middle East. Also known as the "Old Man of the Mountain", he is the legendary head of the sect from which the name Assassin was derived.		The story of how this leading sect, the largest religious group in the Middle East, became the Order of Assassins is a long and complicated one. To put it simply, they adhered to a "stricter, fanatical doctrine."		Even among the sects that did not hesitate to use violence for propagation, they were extreme. They were the only school of thought that preached "obedience to absolute authority." They became an organization and used assassination as one of their political methods. The assassins would stimulate their minds using hashish and pull off things beyond human power. The name Assassin means hashish.		The person that radicalized them to that extent was the Old Man of the Mountain, Hassan-i Sabbah. He occupied a castle in the mountains and built a thorough religious organization using it as a base.		The "assassination organization" that continues to this day is the cog that Hassan-i Sabbah created. It is said that no matter how many years have passed since its formation, the "Old Man of the Mountain" continues to exist in his school. His precise work was unmatched and his alias was known to even distant foreign countries. He hid in the mountains without showing himself, and killed those who went against God. His way of life was an inspiration for European poets.		Hassan's anecdote became legendary while getting dramatized, and eventually the name Assassin became synonymous with "one who performs assassinations." His existence, exaggerated over many years, has become a modern-day illusion no less than the heroes in mythology.		The Old Man of the Mountain, Hassan-i Sabban appears in several stories. He is the face of the unidentified Assassins, and it is said that all those who become leaders of the cult imitate his name and appearance. Or rather, no other way of being is allowed.		In the main story of the Holy Grail War, Assassin class Servants are all summoned as an ãOld Man of the Mountain.ã Hassan-i Sabban is reborn every time one is replaced. Out of the dozens of party leaders, one is summoned to the present day as Hassan...	...their true appearances and names from before taking the name Hassan, from before becoming assassins, forever lost.::Presence Concealment: A+::Conceals all presence as a Servant.	Ideal for covert operations.	Almost impossible to detect if he completely conceals his presence.	However, if he readies to attack, the rank of Presence Concealment greatly diminishes.::40_skill_08_00::::::::::::::::Throw (Dagger): B::The ability to throw daggers like bullets.::40_skill_08_10::::::Protection Against the Wind: A::An Islamic blessing to ward off typhoons.::40_skill_08_11::::::Self-Modification: C::The aptitude to attach and fuse completely different bodies to oneself.	The higher the rank, the further the user becomes from a righteous hero.::40_skill_08_12::::::::::::::::::::::::::0::41_atrus_16a::Delusional Heartbeat::Zabaniya::C::Anti-Personnel::3 - 9::1 person::::Cursed arm. The arm of the evil spirit Shaytan, it excels at cursing humans to death.	Using a lump of ether and a mirror image of the assassination target, it creates a secondary existence which affects the actual target. By crushing the fake image that resonates with the assassination target, he curses the target to death without laying a finger on the actual target.		His assassination methods include nullifying even the most powerful physical defenses, and crushing the target's heart. No matter how solid the armor, it is rendered useless before Zabaniya.		To counter Zabaniya, what is vital is not a high CON (endurance), but a high MGI (magical energy), to prevent a secondary existence from being created.::0::::::::::::::::::::0::::::::::::::::::::
10::ÐÛÐ¨Ð˜ÐÀÐÐñÐË::8::Archer::Gilgamesh::6::6::Male::182::68::Chaotic-Good::B::B::C::A::C::EX::Part man, part god, he is a king who ruled Uruk, a city-state of Sumeria, before the Common Era.	A ruler not just of legend, but who is also believed to have actually existed, he is written about in one of mankind's oldest epic poems, the [font italic=true]Epic of Gilgamesh[font italic=false].		A 2/3 divine and 1/3 human demigod, he is a peerless sovereign of the world and a supreme being who has obtained everything in existence.	Initially he was a tyrant who thought little of his citizens, but his behavior gradually changed after befriending Enkidu. Enkidu was a divine creation made by the goddess Aruru in response to the prayers of the people suffering under Gilgamesh's oppressive rule. Enkidu and Gilgamesh were destined to meet, and they affected one another greatly. At first, Gilgamesh feared and viewed Enkidu as an enemy, but the two soon formed a mutual bond, and later worked as equals to govern the nation. The two of them also defeated the guardian of the forest, the Divine Beast Humbaba, and Gilgamesh would eventually go on to be known as the greatest king on earth, taking possession of every fortune known to man. At this point, Gilgamesh was a dazzling and powerful being that even the gods could not ignore.		A goddess fell in love with Gilgamesh.	The goddess of fertility, Ishtar, proposed marriage to the perfect king, but Gilgamesh bluntly rebuffed the goddess' proposal. He did so because he knew Ishtar was a capricious and brutal witch who ruined men's lives. An angry Ishtar claimed Gilgamesh insulted her and she sent her father Anu's Bull of Heaven to Earth as retaliation. The unleashing of this unbeatable Divine Beast caused seven years of famine and destruction. Gilgamesh and Enkidu worked together to confront the Bull of Heaven and successfully defeat it, further tarnishing the goddess' reputation. Ishtar's anger could not be quelled, so the goddess asked the gods for the death of either Gilgamesh or Enkidu, reasoning that a human killing a Divine Beast is a punishable sin. Ishtar's wishes were heard, and Enkidu slowly wasted away until they died, as they were a creation of the gods and unable to resist their orders.		This was the start of Gilgamesh's downfall.	He was shocked to find that his friend, the only one who could match him in power, was just as capable of death. Gilgamesh was haunted by the fear of this doom, and so he set out on a journey to the underworld in search of immortality. After an arduous trek, Gilgamesh obtained the elixir of immortality. However, as he bathed en route home, a snake drank the elixir, and Gilgamesh was left to die in despair. It is said that snakes are reborn into a new body each time they shed their skin because one drank Gilgamesh's elixir.		Humanity's oldest King of Heroes, Gilgamesh.	Tales of his clash with the gods, his journey to seek immortality, and a great flood over the world...everything in his epic became the archetype and basis for all mythology. His name may not be as recognizable as Arthur or Heracles, but this comparatively nameless figure is the oldest hero king. His overwhelming power truly makes him the strongest Heroic Spirit.::Magic Resistance: E::Protection against magecraft.	It cannot nullify magecraft, but it simply reduces damage of a certain value.::40_skill_09_00::::::Independent Action: A+::A skill that allows movement even without a Master.::40_skill_09_01::::::Golden Rule: A::Not in reference to the golden ratio, but rather the fate of obtaining wealth in one's lifetime.		A billionaire best described as a Goldy. He will never know financial difficulty nor want for anything.::40_skill_09_10::::::Charisma: A+::The ability to command and lead large armies.		With this amount of charisma, it is closer to magecraft or a curse rather than a skill representing high esteem.::40_skill_09_11::::::Divinity: B (A+)::He has the highest aptitude for being a Divine Spirit, but because he hates the gods it has been ranked down.::40_chara_09b::21ÌÝÓ´ÐÛÐ¨ÕÏ02::40_skill_09_12::::::::::::::::::::::1::41_atrus_02a::Star of Creation that Divided Heaven and Earth::Enuma Elish::EX::Anti-World::1~99::1000 persons::::Ea, the Sword of Rupture. The blade that can sever space itself.	A rift created by compressed and clashing winds becomes an artificial fault line that divides spacetime, annihilating everything that stands against it.		There is no way to defend against its destructive power unless the target has an Anti-Purge AC or an attack powerful enough to cancel it out. The damage value is STR x 20, but the MGI value can randomly be added to STR. Its maximum damage is 4000.		However, its damage increases exponentially when Noble Phantasms from the treasury are used as backup.		It is a sword with the power to sever the world, which makes it equal to or even more powerful than Saber's Excalibur. ::0::41_atrus_08a::Treasury of the King::Gate of Babylon::E~A++::Anti-Personnel:: -::::::A key-shaped sword that connects to the Golden Capital.	It bridges space and allows the user to freely take any treasure from the vault.	Though it need not be said, the more treasures that are gathered, the greater the power of this Noble Phantasm.::0:::::::::::::::::::3ö8